Package edu.mit.jwi.item

Provides classes and interfaces that represent the Wordnet data structures.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
IExceptionEntry Represents an entry in an exception file (e.g., verb.exc or exc.vrb).
IExceptionEntryID A unique identifier sufficient to retrieve the specified IExceptionEntry from the Wordnet database.
IExceptionEntryProxy Represents the data that can be obtained from an exception entry file.
IHasID<T extends IItemID> Indicates that the implementing object has an ID object of type T, which is returned by the call.
IHasPartOfSpeech This interface indicates that object that implements it may have an associated part of speech.
IIndexWord Represents an index word object.
IIndexWordID A unique identifier sufficient to retrieve a specific index word from the Wordnet database.
IItemID<T> Indicates that the object is an ID object, and is assocated with a specific class (usually an interface)
IPointerType Objects that implement this interface represent all possible types of pointers that are contained in the dictionary data resources.
ISynset Represents a synset object.
ISynsetID Represents a unique identifier for a ISynset, sufficient to retrieve the synset from the Wordnet database.
IVerbFrame Represents a verb frame drawn from the verb frames data file in the Wordnet distribution
IWord Represents a word (a pair of an IIndexWord and ISynset) in the Wordnet database.
IWordID Represents a unique identifier sufficient to retrieve a particular IWord object from the Wordnet database.
 

Class Summary
ExceptionEntry Default implementation of an IExceptionEntry.
ExceptionEntryID Default implementation of IExceptionEntryID
ExceptionEntryProxy Default implementation of IExceptionEntryProxy
IndexWord Default implementation of IIndexWord.
IndexWordID Default implementation of IIndexWordID
Synset Default implementation of ISynset
SynsetID Default implementation of ISynsetID
Word Default implementation of IWord
WordID Default implementation of IWordID
 

Enum Summary
PartOfSpeech Represents part of speech objects.
VerbFrame Default, enum, implementation of IVerbFrame that does not read from the actual Wordnet database.
WordnetPointerType Default, hardcoded, implementation of IPointerType for Wordnet 2.1 & 3.0.
 

Package edu.mit.jwi.item Description

Provides classes and interfaces that represent the Wordnet data structures.
